Anemia treatment may include:&nbsp;

Iron and vitamin supplements&nbsp;
Red blood cell transfusion for severe anemia&nbsp;
Treating the source of blood loss

Treatment for viral pneumonia may include:&nbsp;

Antiviral therapy&nbsp;
Oxygen

You may have strep throat.


Strep throat is a throat infection caused by streptococcal bacteria. Symptoms are often more severe than with a viral sore throat. Strep throat occurs most often in children ages 5-15, but anyone can get it. Some children have a reaction to the strep bacteria that causes a rash called scarlet fever. Strep throat spreads from person to person from contact with saliva or nasal secretions. If not treated, strep throat may lead to serious health problems such as rheumatic fever, kidney problems, middle ear infections, meningitis, and throat abscess.&nbsp;

